  <TITLE>Handling SingleSelect: set to null value, easier adding of new values</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>My table has several columns, one is titled &quot;category&quot; of type &quot;SingleSelect&quot; and has some &quot;options&quot;. The column is not set to &quot;not null&quot;. When adding a new row, I do not have to add a value for this column. But when I try to edit an existing row which has a value, then there is no option to remove the existing one, I can only change it to a different value/option. Either change the column so SingleSelect implies &quot;not null&quot; or add an option to remove an existing value. When modifying columns of type &quot;SingleSelect&quot;, please consider easier adding of new options. I suppose it is not unusual to realize &quot;I need an option that doesn't exist yet&quot; when adding a new row. This is related to #260 where I lost new unsaved rows when I tried to quickly add a new option which I needed to add a new row...</DESCRIPTION>
